{"id":89289,"title":"[Hip replacement in military personnel].","abstract":"Hip joint diseases and injuries are common for orthopedic pathology among military personnel. Hip replacement is one of the most frequent operations. Authors evaluated hip replacement in 136 servicemen treated at the center of traumatology and orthopedics of Burdenko General Military Clinical Hospital of the Ministry of Defense of Russia in 2010-2013. On the basis of the conducted analysis the main disease groups were revealed, peculiarities of pathology among this category of patients. Authors proposed surgical doctrine for the treatment of this contingent. Effective surgical treatment, in particular, hip replacement surgery, conducted with the use of the proposed principles, as a rule, fully functionally cured patients and contributes to return them in the system that contributes to the strengthening of defensibility of the country.","date":"2014-04-16","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24734432","annotations":[{"name":"Russia","weight":0.814008,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia"},{"name":"Military","weight":0.711976,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Military"},{"name":"Soldier","weight":0.673253,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soldier"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.464781,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Pathology","weight":0.420212,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathology"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.389775,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Hospital","weight":0.385295,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hospital"},{"name":"United States Department of Defense","weight":0.305888,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense"},{"name":"General officer","weight":0.284114,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_officer